    <statement><p>Simplify this expression.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{-t^{2}+tx+30x^{2}}{t^{2}-36x^{2}}}=}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{t+5x}{t+6x}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cross out common terms.</p>
<p>If a polynomial is not in order, we order it by the variable<rsq/>s degrees.</p>
<p>If the leading coefficient is negative, we factor out <m>-1</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{-t^{2}+tx+30x^{2}}{t^{2}-36x^{2}}} \amp = \frac{{-\left(t^{2}-tx-30x^{2}\right)}}{{t^{2}-36x^{2}}} \\
                     \amp = \frac{{-\left(t+5x\right)\mathopen{}\left(t-6x\right)}}{{\left(t-6x\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+6x\right)}} \\
                     \amp = {-\frac{t+5x}{t+6x}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
</solution>
